VRE FOUND IN CHICKEN FEED - USA (02)
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
VRE found in chicken feed - USA 990227222816
[1
Date: Wed, 03 Mar 1999 09:22:53 +0100
From: Mevius, Dr. D.J. <d.j.mevius@id.dlo.nl>

In Europe the prevalence of VRE in chickens and meat products from chickens
is very, or at least it was very high before the ban of avoparcin as growth
promoter. However the VRE strains we isolated were always susceptible to
ampicillin and gentamicin which was reported to be the main difference with
the VRE strains isolated from humans in the USA. The finding of a
multiresistant VRE in chicken products in the USA may suggest that during
processing the product is contaminated with human VRE and that the strain
is not from animal origin.
--
