From: Jean-Pierre LAFONT <lafont@tours.inra.fr>
In France we call this "l'arroseur arrose" from one of the first films by
Melies. The VRE in chicken feed has all the characteristics of the HUMAN
nosocomial US strains (Resistance to ampicillin and aminoglycosides in
addition to glycopeptides: European strains of VRE, human or animal, are
resistant to glycopeptides only). I would strongly suspect contamination
from a human source in the premises during the processing of feed. And yet
this information will be used to add vehement comments on the dreadful
menace animals represent for man etc...We know the song, music and lyrics.
Since the US VREs are more or less clonal, it would be easy to compare the
genomics of the "new" strain to the most prevalent hospital isolates (by
pulsed field electrophoresis for instance).
--
